getDecreaseOrderValidation(uint256).details: Retrieves the validation status for a decrease order count.This function is a view function and is part of the IMarketValid interface.

params.decrOrderCount: The current count of decrease orders.

returns.isValid: Boolean value indicating whether the decrease order count is valid.

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleGranted} event.

isLiquidate(address,address,bool,address.details: Called by `Market` and `MarketReader`.Determines the state of liquidation for a given account and market.This function is a public view function and is part of the IValid interface.

params._isLong: Boolean flag indicating whether the position is long.
params.feeRouter: The instance of the fee router.
params.markPrice: The mark price of the position.
params.positionBook: The instance of the position book.

returns._state: The state indicating the result of the liquidation check:   - 0: Position is not liquidatable.   - 1: Position is liquidatable.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

validCollateralDelta(uint256,uint256,uin.details: Called by `Market`.Validates the collateral delta based on the specified parameters.This function is a public view function and is part of the IMarketValid interface.

params._fees: The fees associated with the position.
params._size: The current size of the position.
params._sizeDelta: The change in size of the position.
params.busType: The type of business operation:   - 1: Increase collateral   - 2: Increase collateral and size   - 3: Decrease collateral   - 4: Decrease collateral and size

validDecreaseOrder(uint256,uint256,uint2.details: Called by `Market`.Validates a decrease order based on the provided inputs.This function is a view function.

params._size: The current size of the position.
params._sizeDelta: The change in size of the position.
params.fees: The fees associated with the order.

validIncreaseOrder((address,bool,uint256.details: Called by `Market`.Validates an increase order based on the provided inputs.This function is a view-only function.

params._vars: The UpdateOrderInputs struct containing various parameters.
params.fees: The fees associated with the order.

validMarkPrice(bool,uint256,bool,bool,ui.details: Called by `Market`.Validates the mark price based on the specified inputs.This function is a public view function and is part of the IMarketValid interface.

params._isExec: Boolean flag indicating whether the execution is internal or external.
params._isIncrease: Boolean flag indicating whether the size is increasing.
params._isLong: Boolean flag indicating whether the position is long.
params._markPrice: The mark price of the position.
params._price: The current price of the position.

validPay(uint256).details: Called by `Market`.Validates the payment amount for a transaction.This function is a public view function.

params._pay: The payment amount to be validated.

validPosition((address,bool,uint256,bool.details: Called by `Market`.Validates a position based on the provided inputs.This function is view-only and does not modify the contract state.

params._fees: The array of fees associated with the position.
params._params: The UpdatePositionInputs struct containing various parameters.
params._position: The Props struct representing the position.

validSize(uint256,uint256,bool).details: Called by `Market`.Validates the size of a position.This function is a public view function and is part of the IMarketValid interface.

params._isIncrease: Boolean flag indicating whether the size is increasing.
params._size: The current size of the position.
params._sizeDelta: The change in size of the position.

function (struct MarketDataTypes.UpdatePositionInputs memory,struct Position.Props memory) view external returns (int256[] memory)
